The AUTOEXEC.BAT is updated. Since `-snapshot` is on, the running VM uses a snapshot overlay. I need to restart QEMU to use the modified image.

{
  "analysis": "The AUTOEXEC.BAT is simplified. Need to restart QEMU to pick up changes (snapshot mode creates overlay on start). Also verify CONFIG.SYS doesn't have problematic drivers.",
  "plan": "Kill QEMU, restart fresh with the modified image, and monitor boot progress.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "kill $(pgrep qemu-system) 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; rm -f /tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 -m 32 -hda /app/isos/win311.img -snapshot -vnc :1 -monitor unix:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock,server,nowait -vga cirrus -net nic,model=ne2k_isa -net user -boot c > /tmp/qemu.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 15 && echo 'xp /2000xb 0xb8000' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock 2>&1 | head -60\n",
      "duration": 20.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
